# AionDB documentation engine

Self-contained static site generator. No external dependencies; Python 3.8+
standard library is enough.

## Layout

  docs/
    build.py               build engine (single file, ~300 lines)
    theme/
      style.css            design tokens + components
      layout.html          page template
    content/               source markdown (organize freely)
      index.md             landing page (URL: /)
      presentation.md      project presentation (URL: /presentation.html)
      license.md           license page (URL: /license.html)
      documentation/       documentation section (URL: /documentation/)
        index.md
      specification-avancee/
        index.md           crate-level implementation notes
    _site/                 build output (gitignored, regenerated)

## Adding pages

Create a Markdown file under `content/`. Optional YAML front-matter:

    ---
    title: My page title
    order: 5
    ---

`order` controls placement in nav/sidebar (lower first). `title` overrides the
first H1 of the page if present.

Sub-section: create `content/<section>/` with an `index.md` inside; the
directory becomes its own top-level entry.

## Building

From the repository root:

    python3 docs/build.py            # build to docs/_site/
    python3 docs/build.py --serve    # build then serve on localhost:8000
    python3 docs/build.py --out PATH # build to a custom directory

## Markdown subset

Supported: headings (# .. ######), paragraphs, **bold**, *italic*, `inline
code`, [links](url), fenced code blocks, unordered/ordered lists,
blockquotes, horizontal rules, basic tables (when written as raw HTML).

Out of scope: embedded HTML pass-through (kept off so generated output stays
predictable), images (add support to `build.py` if needed), nested lists,
footnotes.

If you need a feature that is not in the subset, extend `build.py` rather
than pulling in a markdown library.
